</p>
<p>
Well, I certainly mean to try.  Okay, first we should choke off his summoning abilities with a Stone Prison.  Next we bring Manwe's Blessing and Wind Shield back up.  We're next to the wall of the room, and Trone's in a corridor on the other side of the wall; there's a door in the wall diagonally between him and us, so all we have to do now is wait.  When he opens the door, I drop a Noxious Cloud in his path, just for the extra bit of continuous damage; then he steps up to the plate and battle is joined. 
</p>
<p>
First round, Trone's down one star and I'm down to 1072/1150hp.  Hmm, I missed an annoying number of those attacks; I could crank Tactic up to berzerker, but that does a number on my AC, and I'd rather he not hit me very often.  Let's hold here for now.  Second round, Trone's down three stars, and he misses the turn.  Say, we might just be able to pull this off at this rate. 
