<h4 id="head-e444f12018752e4f9813ad2ea6b3694406f4f8b5">Part 7 of 8</h4>
<p>
Once more unto the breach: 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Mdr 58</strong>, take 2 
</p>
<p>
"Looks like any other level."  Some Air hounds in the same room with me as I enter&#8212;briefly&#8230; <img src="./wiki/classic/img/devil.png" alt=">:>" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
The centerpiece of the level (literally) is another of those clusters of cavern-like rooms carpeted with traps.  The worst this one has to offer is a Great Wyrm of Perplexity and a Grand master mystic&#8230; actually, no, I take that back; I just noticed that one of those '<tt>p</tt>'s is Saruman. <em>[checks notes]</em> Hmm, 7000hp, decent melee damage, a whole raft of nasty melee spells, including a bunch of summon spells&#8212;but he's only speed +10, so with a bit of care, we should be able to pillar-dance him. 
</p>
<p>
I don't have to deal with him yet, though; the three caverns are unconnected, so I can deal with Saruman at my leisure.  First, having swept the east cavern, I punch through to the south cavern and clear out some trolls and a Ranger chieftain, who between them drop: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The Large Leather Shield 'Erente' [+11], with immunity to lightning,  free action, hold life, resist poison, confusion and sound, and reflection 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The metal Boomerang of Beor (+8,+12) (+4), with +4 DEX and speed and  resist acid, lightning, fire and cold 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Now, Saruman's in the north cavern, with a Hell knight, an Ancient green dragon, and a pack of Blink dogs; I'll prob'ly just teleport them out of the way.  First, a bit of creating digging with Thrain's wand to carve out a suitable pillar between the two caverns, then I punch through to let in the hordes.  The dragon and the Hell knight lead the assault, and get teleported away as promised; for the Blink dogs, I just lay down a Noxious cloud carpet to pick them off for me.  And then, Saruman steps up to the plate. 
</p>
<p>
"And right into my claws.  Halt, you multi-colored evildoer!" 
</p>
<p>
Heh.  The pillar trick turns out to be almost unnecessary; Saruman is solidly stunned after two rounds of attacks and dead after two more.  He drops some nice Tomes and Mage Staffs, but nothing I can use.  Of more interest is the Potion of Experience I found in a last-check loot sweep through the caverns&#8212;and considering that I'm already level 50, that really isn't of much interest either&#8230; <img src="./wiki/classic/img/redface.png" alt=":o" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
And that finishes the level; onward to: 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Mdr 59</strong> 
</p>
<p>
"You feel your luck is turning&#8230;"  A 1x5 small level, with nothing to recommend it; fast-forward to: 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Mdr 60</strong>:  Princess quest for 14 Maulotaurs 
</p>
<p>
"You have a superb feeling about this level."  A 3x3 small level, but I won't be going far; the quest room is immediately to my south.  <em>[checks notes]</em> I've faced off against a few of these before; 3250hp, +20 speed, decent melee damage, plasma bolt and fire ball spells, both rendered moot by Trone. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15">  Hmm, according to this, two of their melee attacks do shatter damage; I hadn't noticed that before.  I don't want any earthquakes happening around the princess, so I'll have to lure them out. 
</p>
<p>
That won't be too hard, though; three of them are already headed for me. They fall reasonably quickly, as do the three that immediately follow them from the other side of the quest room.  A bit of dancing lures out two more; for the rest, it looks like I'll have to take it in&#8230; 
</p>
<p>
I take the east side of the quest room first, luring out the three there into a conveniently placed corridor.  Essence of Speed fails at an awkward moment, but fortunately, all it does is give the Maulotaurs a chance to catch up to me.  I loop around to the west half, and one of the Maulotaurs meets me halfway; I lure him back into the entry room just to be safe.  The last two I lure out into another conveniently placed corridor and dispatch with&#8230; well, with dispatch. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
"So, like, what was the point of all that running around and getting all the ugly cow guys to follow us?" 
</p>
<p>
Not sure, in retrospect.  None of the Maulotaurs caused any earthquake effects, which seems odd; I find it highly unlikely that I somehow managed to kill all fourteen of them without any of them hitting me with a shatter attack.  Ah well, a mystery for another day, I suppose.  The quest reward choices are a Fauchard, a Metal Cap or a Halberd; the cap isn't likely to beat Thengel, and the weapons will probably sell for more&#8230; actually, we've already got 2.7 <em>million</em> gold by now, I think that's enough. We can't use either of the weapons, so let's try the cap.  It turns out to be a Metal Cap of Beauty [+7] (+3). 
</p>
<p>
"Don't learn, do you, lad? <em>(zizz)</em>" 
</p>
<p>
What?  It's not like we actually <em>needed</em> the money or anything.  A quick sweep over the level checking for anything interesting nets: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The Metal Scale Mail 'Thodrion' [+11], with sustain STR, CON and CHA,  hold life, and resist acid and cold 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
which on reflection isn't really that interesting after all.  Onward, then, to: 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Mdr 61</strong> 
</p>
<p>
"Looks like any other level."  A full-sized level, finally.  Not terribly interesting, though, beyond a lesser vault (bank) near the middle&#8212;and even that isn't very interesting, except that it netted another spare Wand of Stone Prison.  Moving right along, then: 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Mdr 62</strong>:  Princess quest for 5 Hru 
</p>
<p>
Now, <em>these</em> guys I've had earthquake problems with&#8230;  The level is a 1x3 small level, and Vision reveals that there is in fact no quest room here.  Hmph. 
</p>
<p>
"Wait&#8230; so if the princess lady isn't here, then, like, who was that shouting at all those hooroos?" 
</p>
<p>
A minor bug; the game prints the quest message even if it fails to actually place the quest room. 
</p>
<p>
"Oh.  Ya know, now that you mention it, she <em>did</em> actually sound kinda pre-recorded this time&#8230;" 
</p>
